definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residue and an alpha-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-mannopyranose and beta-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylarabinose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and alpha-L-arabinopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of an alpha-L-fucopyranosyl residue, a beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue and D-glucitol joined in sequence by (1->2) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
